bcal
------------------------------------------
bcal (Byte CALculator) is a command-line utility for storage, hardware and
firmware developers who deal with storage-specific numerical calculations,
expressions, unit conversions or address calculations frequently. If you are
one and can't calculate the hex address offset for (512 - 16) MiB immediately,
or the value when the 43rd bit of a 64-bit address is set, bcal is for you.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.4-2
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libreadline7-8.1-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.2-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libreadline-devel-8.1-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jarun/bcal

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jarun/bcal/archive/refs/tags/v2.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bcal-2.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bcal-2.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bcal-2.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bcal-2.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bcal)
  /usr/bin/bcal.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bcal.README
  /usr/share/doc/bcal/CHANGELOG
  /usr/share/doc/bcal/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bcal/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/bcal.1.gz

